channel.title: Don't Fork My Brain
channel.description: Last 10 notes on Don't Fork My Brain

item.title: wholeheartedness
item.description: wholeheartedness Definition Word Type: n the quality of being fully sincere, committed, or enthusiastic about something, without any reservations or doubt ...

item.title: validation
item.description: validation Definition Word Type: n the act or process of confirming that something is accurate, legitimate, or meets certain standards. It can apply to emotions, actions, systems, or ideas.

item.title: vaguely
item.description: vaguely Definition Word Type: adv in a way that is not clearly expressed, known, described, or decided. Example He explained the plan vaguely, leaving everyone confused.

item.title: unprecedentedly
item.description: unprecedentedly Definition Word Type: adv in a way that has not happened or existed before. Example This was a prime minister who - unprecedentedly - won three big election victories.

item.title: unfiltered
item.description: unfiltered Definition Word Type: a Honest, raw, or unedited, often referring to opinions, language, or emotions. Example Her reaction was completely unfiltered, showing exactly how she felt.

item.title: Uncalled-For
item.description: uncalled-for Definition Word Type: a something unnecessary, inappropriate, or unwarranted, often referring to actions or remarks. Example His rude comment was completely uncalled-for.

item.title: truant
item.description: truant Definition Word Type: n a child who is regularly absent from school without permission. Example Police reports showed that the vast majority of crime committed by children was carried out by truants.

item.title: tardiness
item.description: tardiness Definition Word Type: n the quality of being late or slow. Example I know how frustrating it can be to get behind schedule because of one person’s tardiness.

item.title: stem
item.description: stem Definition Word Type: n The main structural part of a plant that supports leaves, flowers, and fruit and transports nutrients. Example The tree’s stem was thick and sturdy.

item.title: spectrum
item.description: spectrum Definition Word Type: n a range or scale of something, often used to describe a wide array of related things, qualities, or ideas. Example The political party spans the entire spectrum of left to right.
